Police in Port Alfred on Tuesday arrested 16 suspects during detective operations that targeted crimes ranging from serious assaults, malicious damage to property, house breaking and theft, theft of firearm and possession of stolen property.According to police spokesperson, Captain Mali Govender, whilst most of management and personnel spent the day in celebrations for Mandela Day, detectives in Port Alfred Cluster celebrated the day by effecting some arrests. A 24-year-old male was among those arrested in the early hours of the morning, thus far he has been linked to nearly 15 housebreaking and theft cases, said Captain Govender.She added that the suspect also has other three pending cases.The suspect will appear in the Port Alfred Magistrate's Court on Thursday. 